# {{ site.title }}

> {{ site.description }} The site is neutral and source-led — not a debt clock and not party-political. Every figure shows its source, date, and a confidence level (official, provisional, estimated, or calculated).

## About the data

Figures are drawn from official UK and international sources: the Office for National Statistics (ONS), the Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR), the UK Debt Management Office (DMO), HM Treasury, and the IMF for international comparisons. Headline, health, spending, monthly, and international figures were verified against these sources in June 2026. The pre-2010 historical series is a best-estimate reconstruction and is labelled as such.

## Pages

- [Dashboard]({{ site.url }}/): Latest headline figures — net debt, debt as a share of GDP, debt per person, annual debt interest, latest monthly borrowing.
- [Historical timeline]({{ site.url }}/timeline/): UK debt since 1700, by measure and period, with neutral event markers.
- [Debt in context]({{ site.url }}/debt-in-context/): Debt and annual interest set against NHS, education, defence, pensions, welfare, and tax receipts.
- [Interest costs]({{ site.url }}/interest/): The yearly, monthly, and daily cost of servicing the debt, and why the interest rate matters.
- [International comparison]({{ site.url }}/international/): UK debt, deficit, and growth against other major economies (IMF data).
- [Public finance health]({{ site.url }}/health/): Wider indicators — inflation, unemployment, productivity, tax burden, revenue, spending.
- [Big numbers translator]({{ site.url }}/big-numbers/): Turn a large sum into per-person figures and shares of budgets and GDP.
- [During your lifetime]({{ site.url }}/lifetime/): How UK debt has changed since a chosen birth year.
- [Budget simulator]({{ site.url }}/budget-simulator/): A simplified educational model of spending and tax trade-offs.
- [Debt vs deficit]({{ site.url }}/deficit-vs-debt/): Plain-English explainer of debt, deficit, borrowing, GDP, and gilts.
- [Monthly update]({{ site.url }}/monthly/): Plain-English summary of the latest public finances release.
- [Glossary]({{ site.url }}/glossary/): Definitions of the key public-finance terms.
- [Sources]({{ site.url }}/sources/): Every data source, what it covers, and how often it updates.

## Editorial principles

Plain English. Facts separated from interpretation. No party-political blame. National debt is not presented as updating second-by-second. The household-finance analogy is used only with its limits spelled out.
